versive and her strategic localism as resistant to U.S. cultural imperialism. Reyes reads González's and Traba's complex visual and textual production and their intertwined careers against Cold War modernization programs that were deeply embedded in the elite's fear of the masses and designed to avert Cuban-inspired revolution. In so doing, Reyes provides fresh insights into Colombia's social anxieties and frustrations while highlighting how interrogations of taste became vital expressions of the growing discontent with the Colombian state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aArt and societyzColombiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArtxPolitical aspectszColombiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aArt, ColombianxPolitical aspectsy20th century. 0aArt, Colombiany20th century. 0aPop artzColombiay20th century. 7aART / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478004554zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478004554423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478004554.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles